AR 1. When conducting a materiality assessment on environmental subtopics, the undertaking shall
assess the materiality of pollution in its own operations and its upstream and downstream
value chain, and may consider the four phases below, also known as the LEAP approach:
(a) Phase 1: locate where in its own operations and its upstream and downstream value
chain the interface with nature takes place;
(b) Phase 2: evaluate the pollution-related dependencies and impacts;
